<H1>WebDAV Working Groups</H1>
<P>There are three <A href=3D"http://www.ietf.org/"><I>IETF</I></A> =
Working Groups=20
related to WebDAV. These are the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.webdav.org/wg/#webdav">WebDAV Working Group</A>, the =
<A=20
href=3D"http://www.webdav.org/wg/#dasl">DASL Working Group</A>, and the =
<A=20
href=3D"http://www.webdav.org/wg/#dv">Delta-V Working Group</A>. =
Information for=20
each is detailed below. </P>
<HR width=3D"50%">

<H2><A name=3Dwebdav>WebDAV Working Group</A></H2>
<TABLE>
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TH align=3Dleft>Chair:</TH>
    <TD><A href=3D"mailto:ejw@ics.uci.edu">Jim Whitehead</A></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TH align=3Dleft>Home page:</TH>
    <TD><A=20
      =
href=3D"http://www.ics.uci.edu/pub/ietf/webdav/">http://www.ics.uci.edu/p=
ub/ietf/webdav/</A></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
<P>This is the general Working Group (WG) for WebDAV. Generic issues are =
handled=20
by this WG, and it is responsible for the base-level of the WebDAV =
standards.=20
</P>
<P>Joining the discussion list makes you a member of the WG. Here are =
additional=20
details of the discussion list: </P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <DL>
    <DT><STRONG>Sending mail to the list</STRONG>=20
    <DD>Send your email to <A=20
    href=3D"mailto:w3c-dist-auth@w3.org">w3c-dist-auth@w3.org</A> =
<BR><BR>
    <DT><STRONG>Subscribing to the list</STRONG>=20
    <DD>Send a message with a "Subject: subscribe" to <A=20
    =
href=3D"mailto:w3c-dist-auth-request@w3.org?subject=3Dsubscribe">mailto:w=
3c-dist-auth-request@w3.org?subject=3Dsubscribe</A>=20
    <BR><BR>
    <DT><STRONG>Viewing the archive</STRONG>=20
    <DD>There is a <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/w3c-dist-auth/"><I>hypertext =

    archive</I></A> available, and an <A=20
    href=3D"ftp://ftp.w3.org/pub/ietf/w3c-dist-auth/"><I>FTP =
archive</I></A>. (<A=20
    href=3D"ftp://ftp-eu.w3.org/pub/ietf/w3c-dist-auth/"><I>European=20
    mirror)</I></A> <BR><BR></DD></DL></BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR width=3D"50%">

<H2><A name=3Ddasl>DASL Working Group</A></H2>
<TABLE>
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TH align=3Dleft>Chair:</TH>
    <TD><A href=3D"mailto:alexhop@microsoft.com">Alex =
Hopmann</A></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TH align=3Dleft>Home page:</TH>
    <TD><A=20
    =
href=3D"http://www.webdav.org/dasl/">http://www.webdav.org/dasl/</A></TD>=
</TR></TBODY></TABLE>
<P>This Working Group is working on searching facilities for DAV =
repositories.=20
</P>
<P>Joining the discussion list makes you a member of the WG. Here are =
additional=20
details of the discussion list: </P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <DL>
    <DT><STRONG>Sending mail to the list</STRONG>=20
    <DD>Send your email to <A=20
    href=3D"mailto:www-webdav-dasl@w3.org">www-webdav-dasl@w3.org</A> =
<BR><BR>
    <DT><STRONG>Subscribing to the list</STRONG>=20
    <DD>Send a message with a "Subject: subscribe" to <A=20
    =
href=3D"mailto:www-webdav-dasl-request@w3.org?subject=3Dsubscribe">mailto=
:www-webdav-dasl-request@w3.org?subject=3Dsubscribe</A>=20
    <BR><BR>
    <DT><STRONG>Viewing the archive</STRONG>=20
    <DD>There is a <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-webdav-dasl/"><I>hypertex=
t=20
    archive</I></A> available. <BR><BR></DD></DL></BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR width=3D"50%">

<H2><A name=3Ddv>Delta-V Working Group</A></H2>
<TABLE>
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TH align=3Dleft>Chair:</TH>
    <TD><A href=3D"mailto:jamsden@us.ibm.com">Jim Amsden</A></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TH align=3Dleft>Home page:</TH>
    <TD><A=20
      =
href=3D"http://www.webdav.org/deltav/">http://www.webdav.org/deltav/</A><=
/TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
<P>Delta-V is picking up where WebDAV left off, extending the Web with=20
versioning and configuration management support. </P>
<P>Joining the discussion list makes you a member of the WG. Here are =
additional=20
details of the discussion list: </P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <DL>
    <DT><STRONG>Sending mail to the list</STRONG>=20
    <DD>Send your email to <A=20
    =
href=3D"mailto:ietf-dav-versioning@w3.org">ietf-dav-versioning@w3.org</A>=
=20
    <BR><BR>
    <DT><STRONG>Subscribing to the list</STRONG>=20
    <DD>Send a message with a "Subject: subscribe" to <A=20
    =
href=3D"mailto:ietf-dav-versioning-request@w3.org?subject=3Dsubscribe">ma=
ilto:ietf-dav-versioning-request@w3.org?subject=3Dsubscribe</A>=20
    <BR><BR>
    <DT><STRONG>Viewing the archive</STRONG>=20
    <DD>There is a <A=20
    =
href=3D"http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/ietf-dav-versioning/"><I>hype=
rtext=20
    archive</I></A> available. <BR><BR></DD></DL></BLOCKQUOTE>
